==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: alkalic
<hw>alkalic</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having the properties
of an alkali. Opposite of <ant>acidic</ant>.</def> <note>when used of
aqueous solutions, it signifies that the solution has a pH greater than
7.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> alkaline (vs. acidic), basic</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alkali flat</ent>⟦br⟧
